    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.0-dev-312+gc4fcde506\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot test\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux UNEXPECTED 6.0.8-zen1-1-zen #1 ZEN SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Thu, 10 Nov 2022 21:14:22 +0000 x86_64 GNU/Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nAlacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nExcuse me, I'm trying to write my own comment plugin and I found that `nvim_buf_get_mark(0, \"<\")[1]` and `nvim_buf_get_mark(0, \">\")[1]` getting the last visual row position, I don't know why :sob: \r\nI've tried `vim.fn.getpos(\"'<\")` but it seems to produce the same result as `nvim_buf_get_mark` too\r\n\r\nI wish `nvim_buf_get_mark(0, \"<\")[1]` can get the current visual mode's line num, can anyone help me?\r\n\r\nAppreciate your reply :smile: \r\n\r\n```lua\r\nkeymap(\"v\", \";c\", function ()\r\n\r\n    line_start = api.nvim_buf_get_mark(0, \"<\")[1]\r\n    line_end   = api.nvim_buf_get_mark(0, \">\")[1]\r\n\r\n    local lines_table = vim.fn.getline(line_start, line_end)\r\n\r\n    for i, line_str in ipairs(lines_table) do\r\n        -- trim space for line_str\r\n        line_str = \"-- \" .. line_str\r\n        api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, line_start + i - 2, line_start + i - 1, true, { line_str })\r\n    end\r\n\r\nend, { expr = false })\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`nvim_buf_get_mark(0, \"<\")[1]` can get current viusual mode data\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n1",
